The Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission is investigating bribery allegations against 22 Mombasa MCAs who went to inspect the Coca Cola bottling company on Monday over impurities allegedly found in a water bottle.The members of the health committee recorded statements following the swoop by EACC investigators.The MCAs had earlier claimed to have found pieces of cotton wool in bottles of Dasani water, and summoned the company's management to defend itself.Read: Cotton wool found in Dasani water in MombasaDespite requests for more details by General Manager Ibrahim El Khoury last Thursday, the MCAs recommended that the water section of the bottling plant in Kikambala, Kilifi county be shut down.The Kenya Bureau of Standards visited the plant and suspended the production of Dasani water at the plant.Read: KEBS suspends production of Dasani water at the CoastRegional manager Martin Nyakiamo said the suspension will remain until after surveillance inspectors give the production line a clean bill of health.He had urged the public who discover foreign bodies in beverages to report to the committee.On Monday, the MCAs went to inspect the plant and met EACC investigators on their way out.Mombasa EACC boss Simon Cherpka said the committee members would record statements. Lets give officers enough time to complete their investigations. Once they are done we will issue a concrete press statement, he said.Coca Cola recalled water that was bottled between September 16 and 18.The 6,500 half-litre bottles were to be distributed at the Coast.